\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Cross-region generalization on NDWS, raw AUC-PR (left) and CSI (right). Rows: training region; columns: evaluation region. Raw AUC-PR collapses on lowland fires regardless of training region, but the gap is an artifact of the 7$\times $ lower positive-class density in lowland test data---in lift-over-random units (Table~\ref {tab:region}), all four cells achieve $\sim $11$\times $.}}{4}{figure.caption.9}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:region}{{2}{4}{Cross-region generalization on NDWS, raw AUC-PR (left) and CSI (right). Rows: training region; columns: evaluation region. Raw AUC-PR collapses on lowland fires regardless of training region, but the gap is an artifact of the 7$\times $ lower positive-class density in lowland test data---in lift-over-random units (Table~\ref {tab:region}), all four cells achieve $\sim $11$\times $}{figure.caption.9}{}}
